All Implemented Interfaces:

 enum DebugLevel
extends java.lang.Enum<DebugLevel>

Android supports a Log class for debugging that is something like System.out.println. The class implements methods that correspond to different log levels: v() for verbose, e() for error, etc. You write a line to the log like this: Log.e("myclass", "msg");

Because we might want to debug some of our code using a console driver (i.e., not on Android), we need to supply the Log.x() methods. That's done by this class.
